## 🚀 Module Milestones

### 1. Walks Extensions
- **State Machine**: Finalized [startWalk](file:///c:/Users/Martins%20Onyia/Documents/Projects/silver_walks_backend/src/modules/walks/walks.controller.ts#259-282) and [completeWalk](file:///c:/Users/Martins%20Onyia/Documents/Projects/silver_walks_backend/src/modules/walks/walks.service.ts#589-669) with strict time-tolerance windows and status guards.
- **Scheduling**: Added daily and weekly schedule views with automatic filtering based on user role (Nurse/Elderly).
- **Automation**: Integrated `appEvents` to emit `walk.started` and `walk.completed` for downstream consumers (Notifications/Financials).

### 2. Health Profiles & Emergency Contacts
- **Privacy First**: Nurses can only view a narrow summary (mobility level/allergies) of an elderly user IF they have an upcoming or active walk together.
- **Safety Constraints**: Implemented hard limits on medical records (20 conditions / 30 meds) and emergency contacts (max 3).
- **Atomic Operations**: Emergency contact updates use transactions to ensure only ONE contact is marked as primary at any time.

### 3. Admin Capabilities
- **Dashboard**: Implemented a high-performance dashboard using `Promise.all` for parallelized metrics retrieval, backed by a 5-minute in-memory cache.
- **User Management**: Added paginated user listing with full profile joins and an administrative "kill-switch" for account deactivation.

